;	"¼# Pharo on Raspberry Pi

*The [Raspberry Pi](http://www.raspberrypi.org/) is a credit-card sized computer that plugs into your TV and a keyboard. Itâ€™s a capable little PC which can be used for many of the things that your desktop PC does, like spreadsheets, word-processing and games. It also plays high-definition video. We want to see it being used by kids all over the world to learn programming*

![Rasp Spec](http://ssl10.ovh.net/~jeanbaptg/ressources/Screen-Shot-2012-12-24-at-10.59.55-1024x722.png)
Source: http://www.raspberrypi.org/

The idea is to port the Pharo Virtual Machine on Raspberry Pi. 

### RoadMap
+ compile StackVM - done 
+ Sync with github pharo repository - done
+ do a jenkins job - done
+ merge with github pharo repository - todo
+ introduce fast bltbit change (faster UI) - need work.
+ compile CogVM - need  work

### Ressources:
+ [jenkins](https://ci.inria.fr/pharo-contribution/view/RaspberryPi/job/RaspberryPi-Publish/);
